<div id="review_2486854269" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2486854269" />
    <a title="Matthew Quann" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22699228-matthew-quann"><img alt="Matthew Quann" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1642189509p2/22699228.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2486854269?book_show_action=true">Jul 16, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Matthew Quann" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Matthew Quann" href="/user/show/22699228-matthew-quann">Matthew Quann</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22699228-matthew-quann?shelf=pretty-short">pretty-short</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22699228-matthew-quann?shelf=sci-fi">sci-fi</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22699228-matthew-quann?shelf=short-story-collections">short-story-collections</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22699228-matthew-quann?shelf=sff-award-winners">sff-award-winners</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2486854269" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7033938430423128250">I should have been reading Octavia E. Butler years ago! <i>Bloodchild and Other Stories</i> serves as an exceptional introduction to the work of one of SFF&apos;s greats. Across five classic stories, two essays, and two &quot;new&quot; stories Butler shows incredible range in topic and style. The writing here is snappy, readable, and endlessly fascinating. <br/><br/>The eponymous story, <i>Bloodchild</i>, is the type of science fiction tale that burrows deep in the consciousness and lays eggs that hatch for days afterwords. Each of t</span>
  <span id="freeText7033938430423128250" style="display:none">I should have been reading Octavia E. Butler years ago! <i>Bloodchild and Other Stories</i> serves as an exceptional introduction to the work of one of SFF's greats. Across five classic stories, two essays, and two "new" stories Butler shows incredible range in topic and style. The writing here is snappy, readable, and endlessly fascinating. <br /><br />The eponymous story, <i>Bloodchild</i>, is the type of science fiction tale that burrows deep in the consciousness and lays eggs that hatch for days afterwords. Each of the stories that follow present an interesting idea that is presented through a character's specific viewpoint. Rather than great gobs of info dumps, the reader will find out about the world and its concepts in a slow trickle. This could be obnoxious in another writer's hands, but Butler makes the style soar.<br /><br />So, yeah, do read this one. I'll be foisting it upon SFF fans and the normal reader alike. I think it would make for a great bookclub read too! You won't find me waiting long before diving into more of what Butler has on offer.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7033938430423128250" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


